God Bless You Cook!<br>
     Our politics are worlds apart at <br>
times, but I believe our hearts are <br>
marching in step.  Wasn't it you who said<br>
something about wanting so badly to fix <br>
the ills of the world and  jokingly added something like &quot;can I off 'em first and <br>
repent later?'  I laughed out loud <br>
thinking &quot;that has been me at times!&quot;  I <br>
used to say, &quot;I don't want to be <br>
president, I want to be Emperor for a few<br>
months so I can really fix this mess!&quot; <br>
 I've mellowed a lot since, I had to <br>
remind myself that it's a democracy that <br>
I'm trying to mend - you, for one, would hate some of my &quot;fixes.&quot;  Anyway, the point is...I love your heart.  You have displayed compassion with your passion, an admirable partnership.<br><br>
&quot;Those who expect to reap the blessings <br>
of freedom must, like men, undergo the <br>
fatigue of supporting it.&quot;  Thomas Paine<br>
I believe we are both committed to that concept.<br>
   <br>
Your &quot;brothers&quot; were quick to come to <br>
your defense and I commend them for their<br>
undying loyalty.  But, I knew I could <br>
count on you to be tolerant of our honest<br>
differences of perspective as I have seen<br>
how you are ultimately striving for <br>
tolerance and understanding and I salute <br>
you.<br><br>
Ed,<br>
     The &quot;jellyfish&quot; comment was said <br>
with tongue in cheek.  I may be a woman, <br>
but never underestimate my guts and fire.<br>
And don't confuse my idealism with a lack of realism - this country was founded by <br>
idealists! 
